def priority(current_city: int, distances: np.ndarray, unvisited: set[int]) -> np.ndarray:
    cities = np.array(list(unvisited), dtype=np.int64)
    priorities = np.zeros(len(cities))
    for i in range(len(cities)):
        dist = distances[current_city, cities[i]]
        priorities[i] = 1.0 / (dist + 1e-5)
    return priorities
